{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019kCyaqnjyM2MT3eU7TPYAp","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Session Issues Log — 2026-04-03\n2\t\n3\t### 5-3-crash-recovery-resume — create-story (2026-04-03T22:45)\n4\t\n5\t- **Ambiguity in epic definition:** Epic AC says \"no task executed twice\" but doesn't specify mechanism. Resolved with tuple-based checkpoint matching `(task_name, story_key)`.\n6\t- **Ambiguity: loop block resume semantics.** Epic doesn't specify crash mid-loop-iteration behavior. Documented edge case explicitly.\n7\t- **AC #8 (memory/leak for 4+ hours):** Tagged test-provable — structural analysis approach rather than real 4-hour run. Borderline.\n8\t- **Missing `--resume` CLI flag:** Epic mentions `--resume` but that's story 5-4. This story is engine-level only.\n9\t- **No project-context.md found** in the repo.\n10\t- **PRD NFR numbering mismatch:** PRD uses different NFR numbers than architecture-v2.md.\n11\t- **Risk:** Loop block resume logic (Task 5) is most complex — iteration-increment guard needs careful implementation.\n12\t- **Risk:** AC #8 hard to prove definitively via unit tests.\n13\t\n14\t## Token Report — create-story\n15\t- Total tool calls: 22\n16\t- By tool: Read: 10, Grep: 6, Bash: 2, Glob: 3, Write: 1\n17\t- Largest Bash outputs: `git diff --name-only` (~20 lines), `git log --oneline -5` (~5 lines)\n18\t- Files read: 10 unique, 10 total reads (no file read 3+ times)\n19\t- Redundant operations: None\n20\t\n21\t### 5-3-crash-recovery-resume — dev-story (2026-04-03T22:51)\n22\t\n23\t- **Architectural decision:** Story spec's `isTaskCompleted()` with (taskName, storyKey) tuple matching is insufficient for loop blocks — same pair recurs each iteration. Added `isLoopTaskCompleted()` that counts checkpoint occurrences vs iteration number. Deviation from spec but necessary for correctness.\n24\t- **Uncovered lines (97.32%):** Lines ~520, 554, 563-564 are edge cases in loop block iteration advancement for specific crash timing scenarios. Not worth contrived tests for marginal coverage gain.\n25\t- **No `--force` / `--fresh` flags:** Belong to story 5-4, not this story.\n26\t\n27\t## Token Report — dev-story\n28\t- Total tool calls: 28\n29\t- By tool: Bash: 10, Read: 6, Edit: 14, Grep: 0, Write: 0, Glob: 4\n30\t- Largest Bash outputs: `npx vitest run` full suite (~30 lines), `npx vitest run workflow-engine` first failures (~40 lines), `find ... *.test.ts` (~20 lines)\n31\t- Files read: 5 unique, 8 total reads (workflow-engine.test.ts read 3 times)\n32\t- Redundant operations: vitest run 3 times (iterative development — all necessary)\n33\t\n34\t### 5-3-crash-recovery-resume — code-review (2026-04-03T22:58)\n35\t\n36\t- **HIGH bug found & fixed:** Error checkpoints treated as successful completions — `isTaskCompleted()` and `isLoopTaskCompleted()` didn't distinguish success vs error checkpoints, causing failed tasks to be permanently skipped on resume. Fixed by adding `error?: boolean` to `TaskCheckpoint`.\n37\t- **MEDIUM:** Test expectation mismatch exposed by HIGH fix — relied on buggy behavior. Fixed.\n38\t- **MEDIUM:** 3 missing branch coverage gaps addressed — added tests for loop block edge cases.\n39\t- **LOW (not fixed):** `projectDir ?? process.cwd()` fallback never tested — trivial.\n40\t- **LOW (not fixed):** `lastVerdict` null on resume causes conservative retry scope — safe but wasteful, tracked as tech debt.\n41\t- Coverage gaps: Lines 513-514, 563-564 still partially uncovered (unlikely edge cases).\n42\t\n43\t## Token Report — code-review\n44\t- Total tool calls: 30\n45\t- By tool: Bash: 12, Read: 13, Edit: 9, Grep: 0, Write: 0, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n46\t- Largest Bash outputs: coverage output (~80 lines), `npx vitest run` with failures (~30 lines), full suite (~20 lines)\n47\t- Files read: 7 unique, 16 total reads (workflow-engine.test.ts read 8 times — size limits)\n48\t- Redundant operations: 3 coverage runs needed for progressive verification; 8 partial reads of test file due to token limit\n49\t\n50\t### 5-3-crash-recovery-resume — verify (2026-04-03T23:05)\n51\t\n52\t- **BATS failures (253):** Pre-existing, missing shell scripts — not related to story 5-3.\n53\t- **Proof format mismatch:** First `codeharness verify` run failed (0/0 ACs) because proof format didn't match. Rewrote to match expected `## AC N:` pattern with `[PASS]` markers.\n54\t- **AC #8 weak evidence:** Memory usage bounded AC tested with proportional-growth assertion, not actual 4+ hour runtime profiling. Design-level verification only.\n55\t\n56\t## Token Report — verify\n57\t- Total tool calls: 18\n58\t- By tool: Bash: 13, Read: 2, Grep: 3, Write: 2\n59\t- Largest Bash outputs: `npm test` (~80 lines), vitest coverage (~50 lines), vitest verbose grep (~30 lines)\n60\t- Files read: 2 unique, 2 total reads\n61\t- Redundant operations: Coverage ran twice (could have saved output from first), codeharness verify ran twice due to format mismatch\n62\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"452c48b4-eed2-4c96-83e9-8c71df0bbdac","uuid":"ef4d5458-36cb-42da-ab63-1f404fda8ba8","timestamp":"2026-04-02T23:12:16.976Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","content":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-04-03\n\n### 5-3-crash-recovery-resume — create-story (2026-04-03T22:45)\n\n- **Ambiguity in epic definition:** Epic AC says \"no task executed twice\" but doesn't specify mechanism. Resolved with tuple-based checkpoint matching `(task_name, story_key)`.\n- **Ambiguity: loop block resume semantics.** Epic doesn't specify crash mid-loop-iteration behavior. Documented edge case explicitly.\n- **AC #8 (memory/leak for 4+ hours):** Tagged test-provable — structural analysis approach rather than real 4-hour run. Borderline.\n- **Missing `--resume` CLI flag:** Epic mentions `--resume` but that's story 5-4. This story is engine-level only.\n- **No project-c