d 3+ times)","-- Redundant operations: None","-","-### 5-3-crash-recovery-resume — dev-story (2026-04-03T22:51)","-","-- **Architectural decision:** Story spec's `isTaskCompleted()` with (taskName, storyKey) tuple matching is insufficient for loop blocks — same pair recurs each iteration. Added `isLoopTaskCompleted()` that counts checkpoint occurrences vs iteration number. Deviation from spec but necessary for correctness.","-- **Uncovered lines (97.32%):** Lines ~520, 554, 563-564 are edge cases in loop block iteration advancement for specific crash timing scenarios. Not worth contrived tests for marginal coverage gain.","-- **No `--force` / `--fresh` flags:** Belong to story 5-4, not this story.","-","-## Token Report — dev-story","-- Total tool calls: 28","-- By tool: Bash: 10, Read: 6, Edit: 14, Grep: 0, Write: 0, Glob: 4","-- Largest Bash outputs: `npx vitest run` full suite (~30 lines), `npx vitest run workflow-engine` first failures (~40 lines), `find ... *.test.ts` (~20 lines)","-- Files read: 5 unique, 8 total reads (workflow-engine.test.ts read 3 times)","-- Redundant operations: vitest run 3 times (iterative development — all necessary)","-","-### 5-3-crash-recovery-resume — code-review (2026-04-03T22:58)","-","-- **HIGH bug found & fixed:** Error checkpoints treated as successful completions — `isTaskCompleted()` and `isLoopTaskCompleted()` didn't distinguish success vs error checkpoints, causing failed tasks to be permanently skipped on resume. Fixed by adding `error?: boolean` to `TaskCheckpoint`.","-- **MEDIUM:** Test expectation mismatch exposed by HIGH fix — relied on buggy behavior. Fixed.","-- **MEDIUM:** 3 missing branch coverage gaps addressed — added tests for loop block edge cases.","-- **LOW (not fixed):** `projectDir ?? process.cwd()` fallback never tested — trivial.","-- **LOW (not fixed):** `lastVerdict` null on resume causes conservative retry scope — safe but wasteful, tracked as tech debt.","-- Coverage gaps: Lines 513-514, 563-564 still partially uncovered (unlikely edge cases).","-","-## Token Report — code-review","-- Total tool calls: 30","-- By tool: Bash: 12, Read: 13, Edit: 9, Grep: 0, Write: 0, Glob: 1, Skill: 1","-- Largest Bash outputs: coverage output (~80 lines), `npx vitest run` with failures (~30 lines), full suite (~20 lines)","-- Files read: 7 unique, 16 total reads (workflow-engine.test.ts read 8 times — size limits)","-- Redundant operations: 3 coverage runs needed for progressive verification; 8 partial reads of test file due to token limit","-","-### 5-3-crash-recovery-resume — verify (2026-04-03T23:05)","-","-- **BATS failures (253):** Pre-existing, missing shell scripts — not related to story 5-3.","-- **Proof format mismatch:** First `codeharness verify` run failed (0/0 ACs) because proof format didn't match. Rewrote to match expected `## AC N:` pattern with `[PASS]` markers.","-- **AC #8 weak evidence:** Memory usage bounded AC tested with proportional-growth assertion, not actual 4+ hour runtime profiling. Design-level verification only.","-","-## Token Report — verify","-- Total tool calls: 18","-- By tool: Bash: 13, Read: 2, Grep: 3, Write: 2","-- Largest Bash outputs: `npm test` (~80 lines), vitest coverage (~50 lines), vitest verbose grep (~30 lines)","-- Files read: 2 unique, 2 total reads","-- Redundant operations: Coverage ran twice (could have saved output from first), codeharness verify ran twice due to format mismatch"]}],"originalFile":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-04-03\n\n### 5-3-crash-recovery-resume — create-story (2026-04-03T22:45)\n\n- **Ambiguity in epic definition:** Epic AC says \"no task executed twice\" but doesn't specify mechanism. Resolved with tuple-based checkpoint matching `(task_name, story_key)`.\n- **Ambiguity: loop block resume semantics.** Epic doesn't specify crash mid-loop-iteration behavior. Documented edge case explicitly.\n- **AC #8 (memory/leak for 4+ hours):** Tagged test-provable — structural analysis approach rather than real 4-hour run. Borderline.\n- **Missing `--resume` CLI flag:** Epic mentions `--resume` but that's story 5-4. This story is engine-level only.\n- **No project-context.md found** in the repo.\n- **PRD NFR numbering mismatch:** PRD uses different NFR numbers than architecture-v2.md.\n- **Risk:** Loop block resume logic (Task 5) is most complex — iteration-increment guard needs careful implementation.\n- **Risk:** AC #8 hard to prove definitively via unit tests.\n\n## Token Report — create-story\n- Total tool calls: 22\n- By tool: Read: 10, Grep: 6, Bash: 2, Glob: 3, Write: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: `git diff --name-only` (~20 lines), `git log --oneline -5` (~5 lines)\n- Files read: 10 unique, 10 total reads (no file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: None\n\n### 5-3-crash-recovery-resume — dev-story (2026-04-03T22:51)\n\n- **Architectural decision:** Story spec's `isTaskCompleted()` with (taskName, storyKey) tuple matching is insufficient for loop blocks — same pair recurs each iteration. Added `isLoopTaskCompleted()` that counts checkpoint occurrences vs iteration number. Deviation from spec but necessary for correctness.\n- **Uncovered lines (97.32%):** Lines ~520, 554, 563-564 are edge cases in loop block iteration advancement for specific crash timing scenarios. Not worth contrived tests for marginal coverage gain.\n- **No `--force` / `--fresh` flags:** Belong to story 5-4, not this story.\n\n## Token Report — dev-story\n- Total tool calls: 28\n- By tool: Bash: 10, Read: 6, Edit: 14, Grep: 0, Write: 0, Glob: 4\n- Largest Bash outputs: `npx vitest run` full suite (~30 lines), `npx vitest run workflow-engine` first failures (~40 lines), `find ... *.test.ts` (~20 lines)\n- Files read: 5 unique, 8 total reads (workflow-engine.test.ts read 3 times)\n- Redundant operations: vitest run 3 times (iterative development — all necessary)\n\n### 5-3-crash-recovery-resume — code-review (2026-04-03T22:58)\n\n- **HIGH bug found & fixed:** Error checkpoints treated as successful completions — `isTaskCompleted()` and `isLoopTaskCompleted()` didn't distinguish success vs error checkpoints, causing failed tasks to be permanently skipped on resume. Fixed by adding `error?: boolean` to `TaskCheckpoint`.\n- **MEDIUM:** Test expectation mismatch exposed by HIGH fix — relied on buggy behavior. Fixed.\n- **MEDIUM:** 3 missing branch coverage gaps addressed — added tests for loop block edge cases.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** `projectDir ?? process.cwd()` fallback never tested — trivial.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** `lastVerdict` null on resume causes conservative retry scope — safe but wasteful, tracked as tech debt.\n- Coverage gaps: Lines 513-514, 563-564 still partially uncovered (unlikely edge cases).\n\n## Token Report — code-review\n- Total tool calls: 30\n- By tool: Bash: 12, Read: 13, Edit: 9, Grep: 0, Write: 0, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: coverage output (~80 lines), `npx vitest run` with failures (~30 lines), full suite (~20 lines)\n- Files read: 7 unique, 16 total reads (workflow-engine.test.ts read 8 times — size limits)\n- Redundant operations: 3 coverage runs needed for progressive verification; 8 partial reads of test file due to token limit\n\n### 5-3-crash-recovery-resume — verify (2026-04-03T23:05)\n\n- **BATS failures (253):** Pre-existing, missing shell scripts — not related to story 5-3.\n- **Proof format mismatch:** First `codeharness verify` run failed (0/0 ACs) because proof format didn't match. Rewrote to match expected `## AC N:` pattern with `[PASS]` markers.\n- **AC #8 weak evidence:** Memory usage bounded AC tested with proportional-growth assertion, not actual 4+ hour runtime profiling. Design-level verification only.\n\n## Token Report — verify\n- Total tool calls: 18\n- By tool: Bash: 13, Read: 2, Grep: 3, Write: 2\n- Largest Bash outputs: `npm test` (~80 lines), vitest coverage (~50 lines), vitest verbose grep (~30 lines)\n- Files read: 2 unique, 2 total reads\n- Redundant operations: Coverage ran twice (could have saved output from first), codeharness verify ran twice due to format mismatch\n"}}
