{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011kcqqn9iFSS9FX47j1jrhz","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tstepsCompleted: [1, 2]\n3\tlastStep: 2\n4\tstatus: complete\n5\tcompletedAt: '2026-03-17'\n6\tinputDocuments:\n7\t  - prd-overhaul.md\n8\t  - product-brief-codeharness-arch-overhaul-2026-03-17.md\n9\t  - ux-design-specification.md (v1, reworked)\n10\tworkflowType: 'ux-design'\n11\tnote: 'Full CLI UX spec — reworked for architecture overhaul with status visibility, failure detail, live mode'\n12\t---\n13\t\n14\t# CLI UX Specification — codeharness (v2)\n15\t\n16\t**Date:** 2026-03-17\n17\t**Revision:** Architecture overhaul — reworked for visibility, responsiveness, and clear failure reporting\n18\t\n19\t## Overview\n20\t\n21\tcodeharness is a CLI tool. No GUI, no web interface, no visual design. The UX is the developer experience in the terminal: command output, error messages, progress reporting, hook feedback, and proof document structure.\n22\t\n23\t**Core UX principle:** One screen, full picture. Progressive detail. Failures are specific and actionable.\n24\t\n25\t**Target user:** Developer who runs codeharness and checks back later. Needs to understand what happened in 10 seconds, drill into failures in 2 minutes, and never spelunk through log files.\n26\t\n27\t## Command Surface\n28\t\n29\t```\n30\tcodeharness <command> [options]\n31\t\n32\tCommands:\n33\t  init        Initialize harness in current project\n34\t  run         Start autonomous execution loop\n35\t  verify      Run verification pipeline for a story\n36\t  status      Show project state, run progress, and action items\n37\t  bridge      Import BMAD stories into beads\n38\t  onboard     Scan existing project and generate onboarding plan\n39\t  teardown    Remove harness artifacts (preserves project code)\n40\t  state       Read/write harness state flags\n41\t  retry       Manage story retry state\n42\t\n43\tOptions:\n44\t  --json      Machine-readable JSON output (all commands)\n45\t  --verbose   Verbose output for debugging\n46\t  --help      Show help\n47\t  --version   Show version\n48\t```\n49\t\n50\t### Command-Specific Options\n51\t\n52\t```\n53\tcodeharness init [--no-observability] [--no-frontend] [--no-database] [--no-api]\n54\t                 [--opensearch-url <url>]\n55\t                 [--otel-endpoint <url>]\n56\t                 [--logs-url <url>] [--metrics-url <url>] [--traces-url <url>]\n57\tcodeharness run  [--live] [--stop] [--max-iterations <n>] [--timeout <seconds>]\n58\tcodeharness verify --story <story-id>\n59\tcodeharness status [--story <id>] [--check-docker]\n60\tcodeharness bridge --epics <path> [--dry-run]\n61\tcodeharness onboard [scan|coverage|audit|epic] [--project-dir <path>]\n62\tcodeharness teardown [--keep-docker] [--keep-beads]\n63\tcodeharness state [get <key>|set <key> <value>|reset]\n64\tcodeharness retry [--status] [--reset] [--reset --story <id>] [--json]\n65\t```\n66\t\n67\t## Output Patterns\n68\t\n69\t### Status Prefixes\n70\t\n71\tEvery line of output uses a prefix:\n72\t\n73\t```\n74\t[OK]   Successfully completed action\n75\t[FAIL] Action failed — followed by actionable remedy\n76\t[WARN] Non-fatal issue — something to be aware of\n77\t[INFO] Informational — progress update or context\n78\t```\n79\t\n80\t### Symbols for Live/Status Views\n81\t\n82\t```\n83\t✓  completed successfully\n84\t✗  failed\n85\t◆  in progress\n86\t○  pending\n87\t✕  blocked/exhausted\n88\t```\n89\t\n90\t## Command UX: `codeharness status`\n91\t\n92\t### Default Output (One Screen)\n93\t\n94\t```\n95\tcodeharness v0.18.1 | nodejs | enforcement: front:OFF db:OFF api:OFF obs:ON\n96\t\n97\t── Project State ──────────────────────────────────────────────\n98\tSprint: 17/65 done (26%) | 5/16 epics complete\n99\tCurrent epic: Epic 3 — BMAD Integration (2/4 stories done)\n100\tModules: infra:OK verify:OK sprint:OK dev:OK review:OK\n101\t\n102\t── Active Run ─────────────────────────────────────────────────