ad-method install --yes --tools claude-code\n373\t​```\n374\t\n375\t​```output\n376\tInstalling BMAD Core agents and tools...\n377\t✓ Installed to _bmad/\n378\t​```\n379\t\n380\t**Verdict:** PASS\n381\t```\n382\t\n383\t### Agent-Browser Proof (Web App)\n384\t\n385\t```markdown\n386\t## AC 3: Login page renders and accepts credentials\n387\t\n388\t​```bash\n389\tdocker exec codeharness-verify agent-browser navigate http://localhost:3000/login\n390\t​```\n391\t\n392\t​```output\n393\tNavigated to http://localhost:3000/login (200 OK)\n394\tPage title: \"Login — MyApp\"\n395\t​```\n396\t\n397\t![Login page](screenshots/ac3-login-before.png)\n398\t\n399\t​```bash\n400\tdocker exec codeharness-verify agent-browser click \"[ref=email-input]\"\n401\tdocker exec codeharness-verify agent-browser type \"test@example.com\"\n402\tdocker exec codeharness-verify agent-browser click \"[ref=submit-btn]\"\n403\t​```\n404\t\n405\t​```output\n406\tClicked ref=email-input\n407\tTyped \"test@example.com\"\n408\tClicked ref=submit-btn\n409\tNavigation: /login → /dashboard (302)\n410\t​```\n411\t\n412\t![After login](screenshots/ac3-login-after.png)\n413\t\n414\t**Verdict:** PASS — redirect to /dashboard confirms authentication\n415\t```\n416\t\n417\t### OpenSearch Evidence\n418\t\n419\t```markdown\n420\t## AC 5: Runtime logs captured in OpenSearch\n421\t\n422\t​```bash\n423\tcurl -s 'https://search.example.com/codeharness-logs/_search' \\\n424\t  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \\\n425\t  -d '{\"query\":{\"match\":{\"service\":\"codeharness-verify\"}},\"size\":5}'\n426\t​```\n427\t\n428\t​```output\n429\t{\"hits\":{\"total\":{\"value\":23},\"hits\":[\n430\t  {\"_source\":{\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-18T03:42:15Z\",\"level\":\"info\",\"message\":\"init complete\",\"service\":\"codeharness-verify\"}},\n431\t  ...\n432\t]}}\n433\t​```\n434\t\n435\t**Verdict:** PASS — 23 log entries from verification session\n436\t```\n437\t\n438\t## Hook Interaction Patterns\n439\t\n440\t### PreToolUse: Commit Gate (Specific)\n441\t\n442\t```json\n443\t{\n444\t  \"decision\": \"block\",\n445\t  \"reason\": \"Cannot commit — 2 quality gates not met:\\n\\n  ✗ tests_passed: false → Run: npm test\\n  ✗ coverage_met: false → Run: npm test -- --coverage\\n\\nAfter tests pass:\\n  → codeharness state set tests_passed true\\n  → codeharness state set coverage_met true\"\n446\t}\n447\t```\n448\t\n449\t### PostToolUse: After Test Run\n450\t\n451\t```json\n452\t{\n453\t  \"message\": \"Tests completed. Next steps:\\n  → Query logs: curl 'localhost:9428/select/logsql/query?query=_stream:{service=\\\"codeharness\\\"}&limit=5'\\n  → Update flag: codeharness state set tests_passed true\\n  → Check coverage: npm test -- --coverage\"\n454\t}\n455\t```\n456\t\n457\t### SessionStart: Health Check\n458\t\n459\t```json\n460\t{\n461\t  \"message\": \"Harness health: OK\\n  Docker: running (shared stack)\\n  Sprint: 17/65 done\\n  Current: 3-3 verifying\\n  Session flags: reset\"\n462\t}\n463\t```\n464\t\n465\t## Design Principles\n466\t\n467\t1. **One screen, full picture.** `codeharness status` shows everything — project state, active run, results, action items. No scrolling through multiple files.\n468\t2. **Progressive detail.** Status → story drill-down → proof document. Each level adds depth without repeating the previous level.\n469\t3. **Failures are specific.** Never \"exit code 124\". Always: story, AC, command, output, reason, suggested fix.\n470\t4. **Live visibility.** `--live` shows what's happening in real time. Background mode writes to a status file that `codeharness status` reads.\n471\t5. **Actionable everything.** Every `[FAIL]` has a `→` remedy. Every blocked story has a reason. Every action item has context.\n472\t6. **Project-agnostic.** The same UX works for CLI tools, web apps, libraries, plugins. Verification approach changes, output format doesn't.\n473\t7. **JSON everywhere.** `--json` on every command for programmatic consumption. Same information, machine-readable.\n474\t8. **Dense over verbose.** One `[OK]` line per completed step. Summaries, not paragraphs. The user is a senior developer, not a novice.\n475\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_011M8ZBuds1zdWKjWaZPai8m","session_id":"452c48b4-eed2-4c96-83e9-8c71df0bbdac","uuid":"fea19dcc-307c-45aa-8ea5-49a5bdf87fec","timestamp":"2026-04-02T23:13:20.687Z"}
