{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01LThrAibuJppmLGaajz17LV","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01NHuUuWAvbgNUs9jUZAq1gj","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/5-4-run-status-commands.md","old_string":"- [ ] Task 1: Wire `codeharness run` to workflow engine (AC: #1, #2, #3, #4, #9)\n  - [ ] Import workflow-parser, agent-resolver, and workflow-engine modules in `src/commands/run.ts`\n  - [ ] Parse the default workflow from `.codeharness/workflows/default.yaml` (or `templates/workflows/default.yaml` fallback)\n  - [ ] Resolve agents referenced in the workflow via agent-resolver\n  - [ ] Construct `EngineConfig` from parsed workflow, resolved agents, sprint-status path, run ID, and CLI options\n  - [ ] Call `executeWorkflow(config)` and handle the `EngineResult`\n  - [ ] On success: print summary and exit 0\n  - [ ] On failure: print errors and exit 1\n  - [ ] Add `--resume` flag that passes through to engine behavior (engine already resumes by default from story 5-3; flag is documentation/intent)\n  - [ ] Map `--max-iterations` to `EngineConfig.maxIterations`\n  - [ ] Remove the \"temporarily unavailable\" placeholder\n\n- [ ] Task 2: Add workflow-state reading to `codeharness status` (AC: #5, #6, #7, #8)\n  - [ ] Import `readWorkflowState` from `src/lib/workflow-state.ts` in status formatters\n  - [ ] Add a \"Workflow Engine\" section to `handleFullStatus()` that displays: phase, iteration, tasks completed count, elapsed time (now - started), evaluator scores summary, circuit breaker state\n  - [ ] Handle missing `workflow-state.yaml` gracefully (display \"No active workflow run\")\n  - [ ] Add workflow-state fields to `handleFullStatusJson()` output\n  - [ ] Compute elapsed time as `Date.now() - Date.parse(state.started)` only if phase === 'executing'\n  - [ ] Ensure the entire status command completes in <1s (no heavy I/O — `readWorkflowState` is a single file read)\n\n- [ ] Task 3: Write unit tests (AC: #10)\n  - [ ] Test: run command constructs EngineConfig correctly from CLI options\n  - [ ] Test: run command calls executeWorkflow with the constructed config\n  - [ ] Test: run command exits 0 on EngineResult.success === true\n  - [ ] Test: run command exits 1 on EngineResult.success === false\n  - [ ] Test: run command exits 1 with message when no stories ready\n  - [ ] Test: --max-iterations maps to EngineConfig.maxIterations\n  - [ ] Test: status command displays workflow state fields when state exists\n  - [ ] Test: status command displays \"No active workflow run\" when no state\n  - [ ] Test: status --json includes workflow state fields\n  - [ ] Test: all existing tests pass (regression check)","new_string":"- [x] Task 1: Wire `codeharness run` to workflow engine (AC: #1, #2, #3, #4, #9)\n  - [x] Import workflow-parser, agent-resolver, and workflow-engine modules in `src/commands/run.ts`\n  - [x] Parse the default workflow from `.codeharness/workflows/default.yaml` (or `templates/workflows/default.yaml` fallback)\n  - [x] Resolve agents referenced in the workflow via agent-resolver\n  - [x] Construct `EngineConfig` from parsed workflow, resolved agents, sprint-status path, run ID, and CLI options\n  - [x] Call `executeWorkflow(config)` and handle the `EngineResult`\n  - [x] On success: print summary and exit 0\n  - [x] On failure: print errors and exit 1\n  - [x] Add `--resume` flag that passes through to engine behavior (engine already resumes by default from story 5-3; flag is documentation/intent)\n  - [x] Map `--max-iterations` to `EngineConfig.maxIterations`\n  - [x] Remove the \"temporarily unavailable\" placeholder\n\n- [x] Task 2: Add workflow-state reading to `codeharness status` (AC: #5, #6, #7, #8)\n  - [x] Import `readWorkflowState` from `src/lib/workflow-state.ts` in status formatters\n  - [x] Add a \"Workflow Engine\" section to `handleFullStatus()` that displays: phase, iteration, tasks completed count, elapsed time (now - started), evaluator scores summary, circuit breaker state\n  - [x] Handle missing `workflow-state.yaml` gracefully (display \"No active workflow run\")\n  - [x] Add workflow-state fields to `handleFullStatusJson()` output\n  - [x] Compute elapsed time as `Date.now() - Date.parse(state.started)` only if phase === 'executing'\n  - [x] Ensure the entire status command completes in <1s (no heavy I/O — `readWorkflowState` is a single file read)\n\n- [x] Task 3: Write unit tests (AC: #10)\n  - [x] Test: run command constructs EngineConfig correctly from CLI options\n  - [x] Test: run command calls executeWorkflow with the constructed config\n  - [x] Test: run command exits 0 on EngineResult.success === true\n  - [x] Test: run command exits 1 on EngineResult.success === false\n  - [x] Test: run command exits 1 with message when no stories ready\n  - [x] Test: --max-iterations maps to EngineConfig.maxIterations\n  - [x] Test: status command displays workflow state fields when state exists\n  - [x] Test: status command displays \"No active workflow run\" when no state\n  - [x] Test: status --json includes workflow state fields\n  - [x] Test: all existing tests pass (regression check)"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":224,"cache_read_input_tokens":79558,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":224,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":73,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01ELiUhcroCmkW9Cb6Be3ouH","session_id":"452c48b4-eed2-4c96-83e9-8c71df0bbdac","uuid":"c498d74e-9618-4011-b885-3062c7819990"}
