{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CaHxUykfM67dMN7xzov9ry","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Story 5.4: Run & Status Commands\n2\t\n3\tStatus: verifying\n4\t\n5\t<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n6\t\n7\t## Story\n8\t\n9\tAs a developer,\n10\tI want `codeharness run` to invoke the workflow engine and `codeharness status` to display workflow-engine state (iteration, stories, scores, circuit breaker, elapsed time),\n11\tso that I can execute workflows and monitor progress from the CLI.\n12\t\n13\t## Acceptance Criteria\n14\t\n15\t1. **Given** a project with a valid workflow YAML in `.codeharness/workflows/` and a sprint-status.yaml with work items\n16\t   **When** `codeharness run` is invoked\n17\t   **Then** the workflow engine's `executeWorkflow()` is called with a properly constructed `EngineConfig`\n18\t   **And** the command exits 0 on success, non-zero on failure\n19\t   <!-- verification: runtime-provable -->\n20\t\n21\t2. **Given** `codeharness run` is invoked\n22\t   **When** the workflow engine completes (success or failure)\n23\t   **Then** the command outputs a summary: stories processed, tasks completed, duration, and whether it succeeded or failed\n24\t   <!-- verification: runtime-provable -->\n25\t\n26\t3. **Given** `codeharness run` is invoked with `--resume`\n27\t   **When** `workflow-state.yaml` contains tasks from a prior run\n28\t   **Then** the engine resumes from the last completed task (crash recovery from story 5-3 is activated)\n29\t   **And** the command does not re-execute already-completed tasks\n30\t   <!-- verification: runtime-provable -->\n31\t\n32\t4. **Given** `codeharness run` is invoked with `--max-iterations <n>`\n33\t   **When** the engine processes loop blocks\n34\t   **Then** the engine's `maxIterations` config is set to `<n>`\n35\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n36\t\n37\t5. **Given** `codeharness status` is invoked with no flags and `workflow-state.yaml` exists\n38\t   **When** the command reads the workflow state\n39\t   **Then** it displays: current iteration number, phase (idle/executing/completed), number of tasks completed, elapsed time since `started`, and evaluator scores (if any)\n40\t   **And** it displays circuit breaker state (triggered: yes/no, reason if triggered)\n41\t   <!-- verification: runtime-provable -->\n42\t\n43\t6. **Given** `codeharness status` is invoked and no `workflow-state.yaml` exists\n44\t   **When** the command reads the workflow state\n45\t   **Then** it displays \"No active workflow run\" (or equivalent) without crashing\n46\t   <!-- verification: runtime-provable -->\n47\t\n48\t7. **Given** `codeharness status` is invoked with `--json`\n49\t   **When** the workflow state is read\n50\t   **Then** the output is valid JSON containing all workflow-state fields: workflow_name, started, iteration, phase, tasks_completed count, evaluator_scores, circuit_breaker, elapsed time\n51\t   <!-- verification: runtime-provable -->\n52\t\n53\t8. **Given** `codeharness status` is invoked\n54\t   **When** the command completes\n55\t   **Then** it returns in under 1 second (NFR5: status returns in <1s)\n56\t   <!-- verification: runtime-provable -->\n57\t\n58\t9. **Given** `codeharness run` is invoked\n59\t   **When** there are no backlog or ready-for-dev stories in sprint-status.yaml\n60\t   **Then** the command exits with a clear message: \"No stories ready for execution\" (or similar)\n61\t   **And** exit code is non-zero\n62\t   <!-- verification: runtime-provable -->\n63\t\n64\t10. **Given** unit tests for the run and status command wiring and the workflow-engine integration\n65\t    **When** `npm run test:unit` is executed\n66\t    **Then** tests verify: EngineConfig construction from CLI args, run command success/failure paths, status command reads workflow state correctly, status --json output shape, status with missing state file, and all existing tests pass with zero regressions\n67\t    **And** 80%+ coverage on new code paths\n68\t    <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n69\t\n70\t## Tasks / Subtasks\n71\t\n72\t- [x] Task 1: Wire `codeharness run` to workflow engine (AC: #1, #2, #3, #4, #9)\n73\t  - [x] Import workflow-parser, agent-resolver, and workflow-engine modules in `src/commands/run.ts`\n74\t  - [x] Parse the default workflow from `.codeharness/workflows/default.yaml` (or `templates/workflows/default.yaml` fallback)\n75\t  - [x] Resolve agents referenced in the workflow via agent-resolver\n76\t  - [x] Construct `EngineConfig` from parsed workflow, resolved agents, sprint-status path, run ID, and CLI options\n77\t  - [x] Call `executeWorkflow(config)` and handle the `EngineResult`\n78\t  - [x] On success: print summary and exit 0\n79\t  - [x] On failure: print errors and exit 1\n80\t  - [x] Add `--resume` flag that passes through to engine behavior (engine already resumes by default from story 5-3; flag is documentation/intent)\n81\t  - [x] Map `--max-iterations` to `EngineConfig.maxIterations`\n82\t  - [x] Remove the \"temporarily unavailable\" placeholder\n83\t\n84\t- [x] Task 2: Add workflow-state reading to `codeharness status` (AC: #5, #6, #7, #8)\n85\t  - [x] Import `readWorkflowState` from `src/lib/workflow-state.ts` in status formatters\n86\t  - [x] Add a \"Workflow Engine\" section to `handleFullStatus()` that displays: phase, iteration, tasks completed count, elapsed time (now - started), evaluator scores summary, circuit breaker state\n87\t  - [x] Handle missing `workflow-state.yaml` gracefully (display \"No active workflow run\")\n88\t  - [x] Add workflow-state fields to `handleFullStatusJson()` output\n89\t  - [x] Compute elapsed time as `Date.now() - Date.parse(state.started)` only if phase === 'executing'\n90\t  - [x] Ensure the entire status command completes in <1s (no heavy I/O — `readWorkflowState` is a single file read)\n91\t\n92\t- [x] Task 3: Write unit tests (AC: #10)\n93\t  - [x] Test: run command constructs EngineConfig correctly from CLI options\n94\t  - [x] Test: run command calls executeWorkflow with the constructed config\n95\t  - [x] Test: run command exits 0 on EngineResult.success === true\n96\t  - [x] Test: run command exits 1 on EngineResult.success === false\n97\t  - [x] Test: run command exits 1 with message when no stories ready\n98\t  - [x] Test: --max-iterations maps to EngineConfig.maxIterations\n99\t  - [x] Test: status command displays workflow state fields when state exists\n100\t  - [x] Test: status command displays \"No active workflow run\" when no state\n101\t  - [x] Test: status --json includes workflow state fields\n102\t  - [x] Test: all existing tests pass (regression check)\n103\t\n104\t## Dev Notes\n105\t\n106\t### Module Design\n107\t\n108\tThis story modifies two existing command files (`src/commands/run.ts` and `src/commands/status.ts`) and the status module (`src/modules/status/formatters.ts`). It wires the workflow engine (built in stories 5-1, 5-2, 5-3) to the CLI surface. No new modules are created.\n109\t\n110\tThe run command currently has a placeholder that says \"temporarily unavailable — workflow engine pending (Epic 5)\". This story replaces that placeholder with the real workflow engine call.\n111\t\n112\tThe status command already has a rich display via `handleFullStatus()` in `src/modules/status/formatters.ts`. This story adds a new section to that display showing workflow-engine state from `.codeharness/workflow-state.yaml`.\n113\t\n114\t### Key Integration Points\n115\t\n116\t- `src/lib/workflow-engine.ts` — `executeWorkflow(config: EngineConfig): Promise<EngineResult>` (built in stories 5-1/5-2/5-3)\n117\t- `src/lib/workflow-parser.ts` — `parseWorkflow(path: string): ResolvedWorkflow` (built in story 2-2)\n118\t- `src/lib/agent-resolver.ts` — `resolveAgent(name: string): SubagentDefinition` (built in story 3-3)\n119\t- `src/lib/workflow-state.ts` — `readWorkflowState(dir?: string): WorkflowState` (built in story 1-3)\n120\t- `src/modules/status/formatters.ts` — `handleFullStatus()`, `handleFullStatusJson()` (existing, modified)\n121\t- `src/commands/run.ts` — `registerRunCommand()` (existing, modified)\n122\t\n123\t### Run Command Architecture\n124\t\n125\tThe run command follows the Decision 8 pattern (Thin Commands, Fat Modules). The command file should remain under 100 lines. The heavy lifting is done by `executeWorkflow()` which already handles:\n126\t- Sequential step execution (story 5-1)\n127\t- Loop block execution (story 5-2)\n128\t- Crash recovery and resume (story 5-3)\n129\t\n130\tThe command's job is:\n131\t1. Pre-flight checks (Docker, state — already implemented)\n132\t2. Parse workflow YAML\n133\t3. Resolve agents\n134\t4. Build `EngineConfig`\n135\t5. Call `executeWorkflow()`\n136\t6. Print result summary\n137\t\n138\t### Status Command Architecture\n139\t\n140\tThe status command already delegates to `handleFullStatus()` in `src/modules/status/formatters.ts`. Adding workflow-engine state is purely additive — a new section in the output.\n141\t\n142\tWorkflow state to display:\n143\t\n144\t| Field | Display |\n145\t|-------|---------|\n146\t| `phase` | \"idle\", \"executing\", or \"completed\" |\n147\t| `iteration` | Current loop iteration number |\n148\t| `tasks_completed.length` | Number of task dispatches completed |\n149\t| `started` | Compute elapsed time if phase === 'executing' |\n150\t| `evaluator_scores` | Latest score summary (passed/failed/unknown/total) |\n151\t| `circuit_breaker.triggered` | Yes/No + reason if triggered |\n152\t\n153\tElapsed time calculation: `Date.now() - Date.parse(state.started)`. Format as human-readable (e.g., \"2h14m\", \"47m\", \"3m22s\").\n154\t\n155\t### Elapsed Time Formatting\n156\t\n157\tUse a simple helper function (no external dependency):\n158\t```typescript\n159\tfunction formatElapsed(ms: number): string {\n160\t  const s = Math.floor(ms / 1000);\n161\t  const h = Math.floor(s / 3600);\n162\t  const m = Math.floor((s % 3600) / 60);\n163\t  if (h > 0) return `${h}h${m}m`;\n164\t  if (m > 0) return `${m}m${s % 60}s`;\n165\t  return `${s}s`;\n166\t}\n167\t```\n168\t\n169\t### EngineConfig Construction\n170\t\n171\t```typescript\n172\tconst config: EngineConfig = {\n173\t  workflow: parsedWorkflow,\n174\t  agents: resolvedAgents,\n175\t  sprintStatusPath: join(projectDir, '_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/sprint-status.yaml'),\n176\t  issuesPath: join(projectDir, '.codeharness/issues.yaml'),\n177\t  runId: `run-${Date.now()}`,\n178\t  projectDir,\n179\t  maxIterations: parseInt(options.maxIterations, 10),\n180\t};\n181\t```\n182\t\n183\tThe `sprintStatusPath` should resolve from the project directory. The run ID uses a timestamp for uniqueness.\n184\t\n185\t### --resume Flag\n186\t\n187\tThe engine already resumes by default (story 5-3 — it reads `workflow-state.yaml` and skips completed tasks). The `--resume` flag is primarily for documentation/intent clarity. If `workflow-state.yaml` has `phase: completed`, the engine returns immediately with `tasksCompleted: 0` (story 5-3 AC #6). The `--resume` flag can override this by resetting phase to `idle` before calling executeWorkflow.\n188\t\n189\t### What NOT To Change\n190\t\n191\t- `executeWorkflow()` — already handles all execution logic (stories 5-1/5-2/5-3)\n192\t- `readWorkflowState()` / `writeWorkflowState()` — already correct\n193\t- `loadWorkItems()` — work item discovery is unchanged\n194\t- `parseWorkflow()` — workflow parsing is unchanged\n195\t- `resolveAgent()` — agent resolution is unchanged\n196\t- `handleDockerCheck()`, `handleHealthCheck()`, `handleStoryDrillDown()` — other status modes are unchanged\n197\t- `src/modules/sprint/` — sprint module is unchanged\n198\t\n199\t### Anti-Patterns to Avoid\n200\t\n201\t- **Do NOT put business logic in the run command file** — keep it thin (<100 lines). All execution logic is in workflow-engine.ts.\n202\t- **Do NOT duplicate state reading** — use `readWorkflowState()` from workflow-state.ts, not custom file reads.\n203\t- **Do NOT block status on workflow completion** — status reads state file synchronously, no async needed.\n204\t- **Do NOT add live/streaming mode in this story** — that's future work (UX spec shows `--live` but it's out of scope for this story).\n205\t- **Do NOT add `--stop` flag** — graceful stop is not part of this story's ACs.\n206\t- **Do NOT modify the workflow engine itself** — this story is purely CLI wiring.\n207\t\n208\t### Previous Story Intelligence\n209\t\n210\tFrom story 5-3 (crash recovery):\n211\t- `isTaskCompleted()` and `isLoopTaskCompleted()` handle resume skip logic\n212\t- `phase === 'completed'` triggers early exit with `{ success: true, tasksCompleted: 0 }`\n213\t- 95 tests total for workflow-engine, all passing\n214\t- `error?: boolean` field added to `TaskCheckpoint`\n215\t\n216\tFrom story 5-2 (loop blocks):\n217\t- `executeLoopBlock()` manages iteration increment and termination\n218\t- `parseVerdict()` processes evaluator output\n219\t- `evaluator_scores` array grows with each loop iteration\n220\t\n221\tFrom story 5-1 (sequential steps):\n222\t- `PER_RUN_SENTINEL = '__run__'` for per-run task checkpoints\n223\t- `dispatchTaskWithResult()` records checkpoints after every dispatch\n224\t- State is written to disk after every task completion\n225\t\n226\t### Git Intelligence\n227\t\n228\tRecent commits show a consistent pattern:\n229\t- Stories implement the core logic in `src/lib/` modules\n230\t- Tests go in `src/lib/__tests__/`\n231\t- Commands in `src/commands/` are thin wrappers\n232\t- No new dependencies added in Epic 5 — all stdlib and existing deps\n233\t\n234\t### Testing Strategy\n235\t\n236\tFor run command tests:\n237\t- Mock `parseWorkflow`, `resolveAgent`, `executeWorkflow` to isolate command wiring\n238\t- Test that CLI options map correctly to `EngineConfig` fields\n239\t- Test success/failure exit codes\n240\t- Test the \"no stories\" early exit\n241\t\n242\tFor status command tests:\n243\t- Mock `readWorkflowState` to return various states (idle, executing, completed, missing)\n244\t- Test that workflow-state fields appear in output\n245\t- Test JSON output shape\n246\t- Test graceful handling of missing state file\n247\t\n248\tTest files:\n249\t- `src/commands/__tests__/run.test.ts` (may need creation or extension)\n250\t- `src/modules/status/__tests__/formatters.test.ts` (extend existing)\n251\t\n252\t### Project Structure Notes\n253\t\n254\t- `src/commands/run.ts` — 93 lines currently, will stay under 100 after refactor\n255\t- `src/commands/status.ts` — 56 lines, thin wrapper (unchanged)\n256\t- `src/modules/status/formatters.ts` — receives the new workflow-state section\n257\t- All imports use `../lib/` paths per project conventions\n258\t- ESM imports with `.js` extensions (project uses Node.js ESM)\n259\t\n260\t### References\n261\t\n262\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-v2.md#Story 5.4: Run & Status Commands]\n263\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md#FR44 — codeharness run]\n264\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md#FR46 — codeharness status]\n265\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md#NFR5 — status returns in <1s]\n266\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v3.md#Decision 8 — Thin Commands, Fat Modules]\n267\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/ux-design-specification.md#Command UX: codeharness status]\n268\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/ux-design-specification.md#Command UX: codeharness run]\n269\t- [Source: src/lib/workflow-engine.ts — EngineConfig, EngineResult, executeWorkflow()]\n270\t- [Source: src/lib/workflow-state.ts — WorkflowState, readWorkflowState()]\n271\t- [Source: src/lib/workflow-parser.ts — parseWorkflow()]\n272\t- [Source: src/lib/agent-resolver.ts — resolveAgent()]\n273\t- [Source: src/commands/run.ts — existing run command with placeholder]\n274\t- [Source: src/modules/status/formatters.ts — handleFullStatus(), handleFullStatusJson()]\n275\t- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/5-3-crash-recovery-resume.md — predecessor story]\n276\t\n277\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n278\t## Verification Requirements\n279\t\n280\t- [ ] Showboat proof document created (verification/5-4-run-status-commands-proof.md)\n281\t- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence via docker exec\n282\t- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n283\t\n284\t## Documentation Requirements\n285\t\n286\t- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated\n287\t- [ ] Exec-plan created in docs/exec-plans/active/5-4-run-status-commands.md\n288\t\n289\t## Testing Requirements\n290\t\n291\t- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n292\t- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n293\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n294\t\n295\t## Dev Agent Record\n296\t\n297\t### Agent Model Used\n298\t\n299\tClaude Opus 4.6 (1M context)\n300\t\n301\t### Debug Log References\n302\t\n303\tNone.\n304\t\n305\t### Completion Notes List\n306\t\n307\t- Replaced \"temporarily unavailable\" placeholder in run command with full workflow engine wiring\n308\t- Added --resume flag to run command (engine resumes by default per story 5-3)\n309\t- Added \"No stories ready for execution\" early exit (AC #9)\n310\t- Added Workflow Engine section to status display (human-readable and JSON)\n311\t- formatElapsed helper added in formatters.ts (per story dev notes pattern)\n312\t- All 4036 tests pass, zero regressions, 156 test files\n313\t\n314\t### File List\n315\t\n316\t- src/commands/run.ts — rewired to call parseWorkflow, resolveAgent, executeWorkflow; --resume flag now functional\n317\t- src/modules/status/formatters.ts — added workflow state display section\n318\t- src/commands/__tests__/run.test.ts — updated tests for workflow engine integration, added --resume tests\n319\t- src/modules/status/__tests__/formatters-workflow.test.ts — new test file for workflow state display\n320\t- src/lib/run-helpers.ts — formatElapsed and countStories used by run command (pre-existing, dependency)\n321\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Xy8yD9yroHvB5H97Nype24","session_id":"452c48b4-eed2-4c96-83e9-8c71df0bbdac","uuid":"16025939-5cf8-49e4-ba60-c2240056c910","timestamp":"2026-04-02T23:28:55.936Z"}
