ts\"\n\n### AC #7: `codeharness status --json` includes workflow state in JSON\n**Result: PASS**\n- Source: `src/modules/status/formatters.ts` lines 502-525 — `getWorkflowStateData()` returns `workflow_name`, `phase`, `iteration`, `started`, `tasks_completed`, `evaluator_scores`, `circuit_breaker`, `elapsed_ms`, `elapsed`\n- Test: `formatters-workflow.test.ts` \"includes workflow field in JSON when state is active\" — parses JSON output, verifies all fields present\n- Test: \"omits workflow field in JSON when no active run\" — verifies graceful omission\n\n### AC #8: Status returns in <1s\n**Result: PASS**\n- CLI measurement: `codeharness status` completed in 0.255s (wall clock, measured with `time`)\n- The workflow state reading is a single synchronous file read — no heavy I/O\n\n### AC #9: `codeharness run` exits early with message when no stories ready\n**Result: PASS**\n- Source: `src/commands/run.ts` lines 82-85 — when `counts.ready === 0`, outputs \"No stories ready for execution\" and sets `exitCode = 1`\n- Test: `run.test.ts` \"fails when no stories are ready for execution (AC #9)\" — mocks all stories as 'done', verifies message and exit code\n\n### AC #10: Unit tests exist for run command and status formatters\n**Result: PASS**\n- `src/commands/__tests__/run.test.ts`: 28 tests covering EngineConfig construction, executeWorkflow call, success/failure paths, --resume, --max-iterations, no-stories exit, error handling\n- `src/modules/status/__tests__/formatters-workflow.test.ts`: 10 tests covering formatElapsed, workflow state display, circuit breaker display, JSON output, missing state\n- All 38 tests pass, zero failures\n\n## Verification Gaps\n\n1. **Local build runtime execution blocked**: The built `dist/index.js` crashes with `ReferenceError: __dirname is not defined in ES module scope` at line 1878 (from `src/lib/agent-resolver.ts:76`). This is a pre-existing bug not introduced by story 5-4. The globally installed `codeharness` v0.26.5 is from a prior 