{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018zvmmMn2BCNjmGoXTcY6Cy","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Session Retrospective — 2026-04-03\n2\t\n3\t**Session window:** ~2026-04-03T00:25 to ~2026-04-03T02:00 (approx. 95 minutes)\n4\t**Sprint progress:** 14/28 stories done (50%), Epics 1-4 complete\n5\t\n6\t---\n7\t\n8\t## 1. Session Summary\n9\t\n10\t| Story | Phases Run | Outcome | Notes |\n11\t|-------|-----------|---------|-------|\n12\t| 4-3-trace-id-generation-injection | verify (tail end) | **Done** | Was already at verify from prior session. 9/9 ACs passed. |\n13\t| 4-4-source-isolation-enforcement | create-story, dev, code-review, verify | **Done** | Full lifecycle in one session. 9/9 ACs, 100% coverage on module. |\n14\t| Epic 4 milestone | — | **Done** | All 4 stories shipped. Commit `4a35568`. |\n15\t| 5-1-flow-execution-sequential-steps | create-story, dev | **Review** | Story created and implemented. 31 tests, 89.91% coverage. Ran out of time before code-review/verify. |\n16\t\n17\t**Net output:** 2 stories completed + verified, 1 story implemented but not reviewed, 1 epic closed.\n18\t\n19\t---\n20\t\n21\t## 2. Issues Analysis\n22\t\n23\t### Bugs Found by Code Review (fixed)\n24\t\n25\t| Severity | Story | Issue |\n26\t|----------|-------|-------|\n27\t| HIGH | 4-3 | `generateTraceId` accepted NaN/Infinity/negative/float iteration values |\n28\t| HIGH | 4-4 | Path traversal via unsanitized `runId` in file path |\n29\t| HIGH | 4-4 | Silent file overwrite on basename collision — data loss risk |\n30\t| MEDIUM | 4-3 | No segment length cap — unbounded trace IDs possible |\n31\t| MEDIUM | 4-3 | `formatTracePrompt('')` produced empty trace marker silently |\n32\t| MEDIUM | 4-3 | `workflow-state.ts` coverage at 79.06%, below 80% floor |\n33\t| MEDIUM | 4-4 | Stale workspace contamination from crashed runs |\n34\t| MEDIUM | 4-4 | Missing edge case tests for sanitization/dedup |\n35\t\n36\tAll HIGH and MEDIUM bugs were fixed in the same session. Code review is earning its keep — 3 HIGH security/correctness bugs caught before merge.\n37\t\n38\t### Known LOW Issues (deferred)\n39\t\n40\t- 4-3: Duplicate trace ID guard missing; empty runId+taskName produces ugly ID; sanitizeSegment strips non-ASCII\n41\t- 4-4: `deduplicateFilename` counter loop unbounded; hardcoded `/tmp/` base path\n42\t\n43\t### Infrastructure Issues\n44\t\n45\t- **`codeharness verify` precondition failure:** The verify command checks global harness state flags (`tests_passed`, `coverage_met`) which are not set by manual test runs. Workaround: verify manually. This is a harness tooling gap.\n46\t- **`AGENTS.md` stale:** Verify command flags missing entries for new modules (`agent-dispatch.ts`, `agent-resolver.ts`, `session-manager.ts`, `trace-id.ts`, `source-isolation.ts`). Documentation debt accumulating — 5 modules behind now.\n47\t- **Pre-existing TS errors:** `src/commands/__tests__/run.test.ts` has 2 pre-existing type errors unrelated to current work.\n48\t\n49\t---\n50\t\n51\t## 3. Cost Analysis\n52\t\n53\t### Parent-Level Costs (from cost-report.md, prior session data)\n54\t\n55\tThe cost report covers the prior session (stories through Epic 2). Key structural observations:\n56\t\n57\t- **Total API cost:** $37.08 across 288 calls for 7 stories\n58\t- **Avg cost/story:** $4.45\n59\t- **Dominant cost:** Cache reads at 61% ($22.62) — expected for long-context sessions\n60\t- **Verify phase:** 43.8% of total cost ($16.24) — nearly half of all spending is on verification\n61\t\n62\t### Subagent Token Report (this session)\n63\t\n64\tAggregated from `.session-issues.md` token reports:\n65\t\n66\t| Subagent Phase | Tool Calls | Top Tools |\n67\t|---------------|------------|-----------|\n68\t| 4-3 create-story | 14 | Read: 5, Grep: 4, Glob: 3 |\n69\t| 4-3 dev-story | 14 | Edit: 6, Read: 5, Bash: 4 |\n70\t| 4-3 code-review | 23 | Bash: 12, Read: 7, Edit: 5 |\n71\t| 4-3 verification | 12 | Bash: 7, Read: 3, Grep: 2 |\n72\t| 4-4 create-story | 12 | Read: 7, Grep: 3 |\n73\t| 4-4 dev-story | 15 | Read: 5, Bash: 4, Grep: 4 |\n74\t| 4-4 code-review | 22 | Bash: 9, Read: 7, Edit: 7 |\n75\t| 4-4 verification | 12 | Bash: 7, Read: 3, Grep: 2 |\n76\t| 5-1 create-story | 18 | Read: 12, Glob: 5, Bash: 2 |\n77\t| 5-1 dev-story | 22 | Read: 13, Bash: 6, Edit: 4 |\n78\t| **Total** | **164** | Read: 67, Bash: 51, Edit: 22, Grep: 18 |\n79\t\n80\t### Observations\n81\t\n82\t- **Code review is the most tool-heavy phase** (22-23 calls) — Bash-heavy because it runs tests after each fix.\n83\t- **Read dominates** at 67/164 calls (41%). The 5-1 create-story phase read 12 unique files — story creation requires reading architecture, PRD, epics, and existing modules.\n84\t- **Redundant operations detected:**\n85\t  - 4-3 verification: `codeharness verify` called twice\n86\t  - 4-4 verification: Coverage run twice (default + targeted)\n87\t  - 4-4 create-story: Two Grep calls to `source_access` could have been one\n88\t  - 4-3 verification: Architecture doc `architecture-v2.md` read twice\n89\t- **Largest Bash outputs:** Coverage runs (80-160 lines) dominate. Test suite runs are 20-50 lines.\n90\t\n91\t### Estimated session cost\n92\t\n93\tAt ~164 subagent tool calls plus orchestrator overhead, estimated this session cost **$10-14** (extrapolating from prior session's $4.45/story rate, 2.5 story-equivalents completed).\n94\t\n95\t---\n96\t\n97\t## 4. What Went Well\n98\t\n99\t1. **Full-lifecycle velocity:** Story 4-4 went from backlog to verified in a single session (~45 min for create+dev+review+verify). The pipeline is working.\n100\t2. **Code review catching real bugs:** 3 HIGH severity bugs caught (path traversal, data loss, input validation). These would have been production defects.\n101\t3. **Epic 4 completed:** All 4 stories (agent dispatch, session management, trace IDs, source isolation) shipped and verified.\n102\t4. **Test quality:** 100% coverage on both trace-id.ts and source-isolation.ts modules. 31 tests written for 5-1 in dev phase alone.\n103\t5. **Zero retries this session:** All stories completed on first attempt — no stuck/failed cycles.\n104\t6. **Session issues log is working:** Subagent self-reporting produced actionable data for this retro.\n105\t\n106\t---\n107\t\n108\t## 5. What Went Wrong\n109\t\n110\t1. **Time budget exhaustion:** Story 5-1 got through dev but couldn't complete code-review or verify. It's stuck at \"review\" status — needs manual follow-up.\n111\t2. **`codeharness verify` is unreliable:** Fails on harness state flags that aren't set during subagent runs. This forced manual verification workarounds in both 4-3 and 4-4.\n112\t3. **AGENTS.md documentation debt:** 5 new modules have no AGENTS.md entries. The verify command flags this every time, burning cycles on a known-stale doc.\n113\t4. **Cost report stale:** `codeharness stats --save` requires `session-logs/` directory which doesn't exist for this session type. The cost report only covers the prior session's data.\n114\t5. **Sprint state file divergence:** `ralph/.state-snapshot.json` shows 4-4 as \"verifying\" and 5-1 as \"backlog\" — but sprint-status.yaml shows 4-4 as done and 5-1 as review. State files are out of sync.\n115\t\n116\t---\n117\t\n118\t## 6. Lessons Learned\n119\t\n120\t### Patterns to Repeat\n121\t\n122\t- **Code review as a mandatory gate:** Every HIGH bug this session was caught by code review, not tests. The adversarial review phase is load-bearing.\n123\t- **Session issues log:** Self-reported token data from subagents made cost analysis possible without working harness stats.\n124\t- **Pure-logic module design:** Both trace-id and source-isolation achieved 100% coverage because they have no I/O dependencies. This pattern works.\n125\t\n126\t### Patterns to Avoid\n127\t\n128\t- **Running `codeharness verify` without checking preconditions:** Wastes a full invocation cycle. Either fix the verify command or skip it when flags aren't set.\n129\t- **Running coverage twice:** Once is enough. The second targeted run is redundant when the first already reports per-file coverage.\n130\t- **Starting a new story late in a session:** 5-1 was started knowing time was short. It would have been cleaner to stop after Epic 4 closure.\n131\t\n132\t---\n133\t\n134\t## 7. Action Items\n135\t\n136\t| # | Action | Priority | Owner |\n137\t|---|--------|----------|-------|\n138\t| 1 | Complete code-review and verify for story 5-1 | HIGH | Next session |\n139\t| 2 | Fix `codeharness verify` to work without pre-set harness state flags | MEDIUM | Backlog |\n140\t| 3 | Update `src/lib/AGENTS.md` with entries for agent-dispatch, agent-resolver, session-manager, trace-id, source-isolation modules | MEDIUM | Next session |\n141\t| 4 | Fix `codeharness stats --save` to work for non-ralph sessions | LOW | Backlog |\n142\t| 5 | Sync `ralph/.state-snapshot.json` with `sprint-state.json` | LOW | Next session |\n143\t| 6 | Fix pre-existing TS errors in `src/commands/__tests__/run.test.ts` | LOW | Backlog |\n144\t| 7 | Address deferred LOW issues from 4-3 and 4-4 code reviews | LOW | Backlog |\n145\t\n146\t---\n147\t\n148\t# Session Retrospective — 2026-04-03 (Session 2)\n149\t\n150\t**Timestamp:** 2026-04-03T02:00Z\n151\t**Session window:** ~2026-04-03T01:53 to ~2026-04-03T02:15 (approx. 22 minutes)\n152\t**Sprint progress:** 15/28 stories done (53.6%), Epics 1-4 complete, Epic 5 started\n153\t\n154\t---\n155\t\n156\t## 1. Session Summary\n157\t\n158\tThis session picked up story 5-1-flow-execution-sequential-steps at `review` status and drove it to `done`. No new stories were started.\n159\t\n160\t| Story | Phases Run | Outcome | Notes |\n161\t|-------|-----------|---------|-------|\n162\t| 5-1-flow-execution-sequential-steps | code-review, verification, proof-doc fix, AGENTS.md update | **Done** | 14/14 ACs verified. Commit `b983273`. |\n163\t\n164\t**Activities completed:**\n165\t1. Code review found 2 HIGH bugs and 2 MEDIUM issues — all fixed\n166\t2. Test-provable verification: 14/14 ACs passed, 3963 tests green, 99.2% stmt coverage on workflow-engine.ts\n167\t3. Proof document formatting fix (needed `**Tier:**` bold format)\n168\t4. `src/lib/AGENTS.md` updated to include `source-isolation.ts` and `workflow-engine.ts`\n169\t\n170\t---\n171\t\n172\t## 2. Issues Analysis\n173\t\n174\t### Bugs Found by Code Review (fixed)\n175\t\n176\t| Severity | Issue |\n177\t|----------|-------|\n178\t| HIGH | Per-story RATE_LIMIT/NETWORK/SDK_INIT errors did not halt the outer flow loop — only the inner work-items loop. Catastrophic failures would be silently swallowed. |\n179\t| HIGH | Dispatch failures did not record a TaskCheckpoint in workflow state, violating AC #13. Crash recovery would lose track of failed tasks. |\n180\t| MEDIUM | Coverage gaps — 8 new tests added. Coverage improved to 99.2% stmt / 87% branch. |\n181\t\n182\t### LOW Issues Deferred (not fixed)\n183\t\n184\t- Duplicate checkpoint creation logic in `dispatchTask` else branch\n185\t- `handleDispatchError` and `recordErrorInState` could be merged\n186\t- `warn()` calls for skipped tasks don't propagate to `EngineResult.errors`\n187\t- Branch coverage at 87% — remaining uncovered branches are defensive null checks on YAML parse results\n188\t- No integration test verifying actual YAML parsing (all YAML mocked)\n189\t\n190\t### Infrastructure Issues\n191\t\n192\t- **AGENTS.md was stale** — missing entries for `source-isolation.ts` and `workflow-engine.ts`. Fixed in this session.\n193\t- **Prior action item resolved:** Action item #1 from Session 1 (\"Complete code-review and verify for story 5-1\") is now done.\n194\t- **Prior action item resolved:** Action item #3 from Session 1 (\"Update AGENTS.md\") is now partially addressed (2 of 5 missing modules added).\n195\t\n196\t---\n197\t\n198\t## 3. Cost Analysis\n199\t\n200\t### Subagent Token Report (this session only)\n201\t\n202\tFrom `.session-issues.md` token reports for the 5-1 phases that ran this session:\n203\t\n204\t| Subagent Phase | Tool Calls | Top Tools |\n205\t|---------------|------------|-----------|\n206\t| 5-1 code-review | 23 | Read: 10, Bash: 9, Edit: 5, Glob: 2, Skill: 1 |\n207\t| **Session Total** | **23** | Read: 10, Bash: 9, Edit: 5, Glob: 2, Skill: 1 |\n208\t\n209\tNote: The verification phase for 5-1 is not in the session issues log — it likely ran as part of the orchestrator or was not instrumented. The proof document and AGENTS.md update were additional orchestrator-level actions.\n210\t\n211\t### Observations\n212\t\n213\t- **Read-heavy session:** 10/23 tool calls (43%) were Read. Code review needs to read the implementation, tests, architecture, and existing code to find bugs.\n214\t- **Bash-heavy for code review:** 9 Bash calls — running tests after each fix. This is inherent to the fix-verify loop.\n215\t- **Redundant operations:** Coverage grep ran 3 times with different patterns (could be 1 call with combined pattern).\n216\t- **Largest Bash outputs:** Coverage run (~80 lines), vitest full suite (~10 lines), git diff --name-only (~11 lines).\n217\t- **Estimated session cost:** ~$3-4 (1 code-review phase + verification + minor fixups). This session was efficient — minimal waste.\n218\t\n219\t### Cumulative Cost Tracking\n220\t\n221\t| Session | Stories Completed | Estimated Cost | Cost/Story |\n222\t|---------|-------------------|---------------|------------|\n223\t| Prior sessions (Epics 1-2) | 7 | $37.08 | $4.45 |\n224\t| Session 1 (2026-04-03, early) | 2.5 | ~$12 | ~$4.80 |\n225\t| Session 2 (2026-04-03, late) | 0.5 (review+verify) | ~$3.50 | ~$7.00* |\n226\t\n227\t*Higher per-story cost for Session 2 is misleading — this was just the tail end (review+verify) of a story that was mostly built in Session 1.\n228\t\n229\t---\n230\t\n231\t## 4. What Went Well\n232\t\n233\t1. **Code review found 2 critical flow-control bugs.** The outer loop would have silently continued past catastrophic errors (RATE_LIMIT, NETWORK, SDK_INIT). This is exactly the kind of bug that only shows up in production.\n234\t2. **Clean verification:** 14/14 ACs passed on first attempt. No re-runs needed.\n235\t3. **AGENTS.md debt partially cleared.** Two missing module entries added.\n236\t4. **Focused session:** Single story, single goal, completed efficiently in ~22 minutes.\n237\t5. **Action items from Session 1 addressed:** The top priority action item (complete 5-1 review) is done.\n238\t\n239\t---\n240\t\n241\t## 5. What Went Wrong\n242\t\n243\t1. **AGENTS.md still has gaps.** Only `source-isolation.ts` and `workflow-engine.ts` were added. Still missing: `agent-dispatch.ts`, `agent-resolver.ts`, `session-manager.ts`, `trace-id.ts`.\n244\t2. **Verification phase not instrumented.** No token report for the 5-1 verification subagent — either it wasn't logged or ran inline. This is a gap in observability.\n245\t3. **`codeharness stats` still broken** for non-ralph sessions. No session-logs directory exists. Cost analysis relies entirely on manual extrapolation from subagent token reports.\n246\t4. **Coverage grep ran 3 times** during code review with different patterns — minor waste but symptomatic of the \"grep-and-check\" loop.\n247\t\n248\t---\n249\t\n250\t## 6. Lessons Learned\n251\t\n252\t### Patterns to Repeat\n253\t\n254\t- **Review-then-verify in a dedicated session works.** Separating the review/verify from the dev phase gave a clean, focused session with no context-switching.\n255\t- **Code review on flow-control logic is essential.** Error-handling paths in orchestrators are where the worst bugs hide. Both HIGH bugs were in error-handling branches.\n256\t\n257\t### Patterns to Avoid\n258\t\n259\t- **Multiple coverage grep patterns.** Use a single grep with OR pattern or just read the coverage summary file directly.\n260\t- **Leaving AGENTS.md updates incomplete.** If updating, update all missing entries in one pass — don't leave partial debt.\n261\t\n262\t---\n263\t\n264\t## 7. Action Items\n265\t\n266\t| # | Action | Priority | Owner | Status |\n267\t|---|--------|----------|-------|--------|\n268\t| 1 | ~~Complete code-review and verify for story 5-1~~ | ~~HIGH~~ | ~~Next session~~ | DONE |\n269\t| 2 | Fix `codeharness verify` to work without pre-set harness state flags | MEDIUM | Backlog | Open |\n270\t| 3 | Update `src/lib/AGENTS.md` — still missing: agent-dispatch, agent-resolver, session-manager, trace-id | MEDIUM | Next session | Partial |\n271\t| 4 | Fix `codeharness stats --save` to work for non-ralph sessions | LOW | Backlog | Open |\n272\t| 5 | Sync `ralph/.state-snapshot.json` with `sprint-state.json` | LOW | Next session | Open |\n273\t| 6 | Fix pre-existing TS errors in `src/commands/__tests__/run.test.ts` | LOW | Backlog | Open |\n274\t| 7 | Address deferred LOW issues from 4-3, 4-4, and 5-1 code reviews | LOW | Backlog | Open |\n275\t| 8 | Add integration test for actual YAML parsing (not mocked) in workflow-engine | LOW | Backlog | New |\n276\t\n277\t---\n278\t\n279\t# Session Retrospective — 2026-04-03 (Session 3)\n280\t\n281\t**Timestamp:** 2026-04-03T02:45Z\n282\t**Session window:** ~2026-04-03T02:12 to ~2026-04-03T02:39 (approx. 27 minutes)\n283\t**Sprint progress:** 17/28 stories done (60.7%), Epics 1-4 complete, Epic 5 at 2/4\n284\t\n285\t---\n286\t\n287\t## 1. Session Summary\n288\t\n289\tThis session completed one story end-to-end within a single ralph iteration (iteration #8).\n290\t\n291\t| Story | Phases Run | Outcome | Notes |\n292\t|-------|-----------|---------|-------|\n293\t| 5-2-flow-execution-loop-blocks | create-story, dev-story, code-review, test-provable verification | **Done** | Full lifecycle in ~27 minutes. 10/10 ACs passed. Commit `1219d18`. |\n294\t\n295\t**Key deliverables:**\n296\t- `executeLoopBlock()` — loop block execution with termination on pass/maxIterations/circuit-breaker\n297\t- `parseVerdict()` — EvaluatorVerdict JSON parsing from dispatch output\n298\t- `buildRetryPrompt()` — finding injection into retry prompts\n299\t- `getFailedItems()` — failed-story-only retry filtering\n300\t- 27+ new tests, 3992 total tests passing, 96.37% statement coverage on workflow-engine.ts\n301\t\n302\t---\n303\t\n304\t## 2. Issues Analysis\n305\t\n306\t### Bugs Found by Code Review (fixed)\n307\t\n308\t| Severity | Issue | Impact |\n309\t|----------|-------|--------|\n310\t| HIGH | **Stale verdict bug** — verdict from a previous loop iteration could persist and cause premature loop termination on the next pass | Correctness: loop would exit early based on old evaluation results |\n311\t| HIGH | **80-line code duplication** — loop block dispatch logic duplicated the sequential step dispatch logic nearly verbatim | Maintainability: two copies of error handling, checkpoint logic, state updates that would diverge over time |\n312\t| HIGH | **Uncovered branches in duplicate code** — the duplicated code paths had no dedicated test coverage | Quality: bugs in the duplicate path would go undetected |\n313\t\n314\tAll three HIGH issues were fixed during code review before verification.\n315\t\n316\t### MEDIUM Issues (fixed)\n317\t\n318\tPer the parent session summary, 3 MEDIUM issues were also addressed during code review, likely related to coverage gaps and edge case handling.\n319\t\n320\t### Infrastructure Issues\n321\t\n322\t- **Session issues log stale** — `.session-issues.md` still contains only placeholder entries from 2026-03-18. The subagents this session did not write to it. The session issues log mechanism is non-functional for ralph-driven sessions.\n323\t- **`codeharness stats` still broken** — `stats --save` and `stats --json` both fail with \"No session-logs/ directory found.\" Cost analysis remains manual.\n324\t- **`ralph/.state-snapshot.json` divergence** — Shows `sprint.done: 12` but sprint-status.yaml shows 17 done. The state snapshot does not update Epic 5 stories as done (shows `storiesDone: 0` for Epic 5 despite 2 stories completed).\n325\t\n326\t---\n327\t\n328\t## 3. Cost Analysis\n329\t\n330\t### Session-Level Metrics\n331\t\n332\t| Metric | Value |\n333\t|--------|-------|\n334\t| Ralph iteration | #8 (of the current ralph run) |\n335\t| Log file size | 2.42 MB (`claude_output_2026-04-03_02-12-22.log`) |\n336\t| Session wall time | ~27 minutes |\n337\t| Phases completed | 4 (create-story, dev-story, code-review, verification) |\n338\t\n339\t### Estimated Token Usage\n340\t\n341\tBased on log file size (2.42 MB of stream-json output) and prior session correlations:\n342\t- Estimated API calls: ~15-25 (4 phases, each 4-7 tool calls)\n343\t- Estimated session cost: **~$4-5** (single story, full lifecycle)\n344\t- Cost per phase (estimated): create-story ~$0.50, dev-story ~$1.50, code-review ~$1.50, verification ~$0.75\n345\t\n346\t### Subagent Analysis (from parent session live log)\n347\t\n348\tThe parent orchestrator launched this iteration at 02:12:22 and it completed at 02:39. The background retro agent consumed 23+ tool calls reading logs and state files — indicating the retro itself is a significant cost center.\n349\t\n350\tFrom the parent's output summary:\n351\t- 10/10 ACs verified on first attempt\n352\t- 3992/3992 tests passing\n353\t- 96.37% coverage on workflow-engine.ts\n354\t- 3 HIGH + 3 MEDIUM bugs found and fixed\n355\t\n356\t### Cumulative Cost Tracking\n357\t\n358\t| Session | Stories Completed | Estimated Cost | Cost/Story |\n359\t|---------|-------------------|---------------|------------|\n360\t| Prior sessions (Epics 1-2) | 7 | $37.08 | $4.45 |\n361\t| Session 1 (2026-04-03, early) | 2.5 | ~$12 | ~$4.80 |\n362\t| Session 2 (2026-04-03, late) | 0.5 (review+verify) | ~$3.50 | ~$7.00* |\n363\t| **Session 3 (this)** | **1** | **~$4.50** | **~$4.50** |\n364\t| **Cumulative** | **11** | **~$57** | **~$5.18** |\n365\t\n366\t*Session 2 cost/story is misleading — it was the tail end of a story built in Session 1.\n367\t\n368\t---\n369\t\n370\t## 4. What Went Well\n371\t\n372\t1. **Full lifecycle in one iteration.** Story 5-2 went from backlog to verified in a single 27-minute ralph iteration. This is the fastest full-lifecycle story completion yet.\n373\t2. **All phases passed on first attempt.** No retries, no stuck phases, no timeouts. The pipeline ran clean.\n374\t3. **Code review caught 3 HIGH bugs.** The stale verdict bug would have caused incorrect loop behavior in production. The 80-line duplication was a significant maintenance risk. Code review continues to earn its keep.\n375\t4. **High coverage.** 96.37% statement, 88.75% branch, 100% function coverage on the primary module. 27 new tests added.\n376\t5. **Budget adherence.** Completed in 27 minutes within a 30-minute timeout window. No timeout, no waste.\n377\t6. **Sprint velocity.** With 17/28 stories done (60.7%), the project is past the halfway mark. Epic 5 is at 50% (2/4).\n378\t\n379\t---\n380\t\n381\t## 5. What Went Wrong\n382\t\n383\t1. **Session issues log is non-functional.** `.session-issues.md` was not updated by any subagent this session. It still contains placeholder data from 2026-03-18. Without subagent self-reporting, cost analysis and issue tracking rely entirely on log file archaeology.\n384\t2. **`ralph/.state-snapshot.json` is increasingly stale.** Shows `sprint.done: 12` vs actual 17. Epic 5 `storiesDone: 0` despite 2 stories completed. The snapshot update mechanism is broken or not running after story completion.\n385\t3. **`codeharness stats` still broken.** Third consecutive session where cost reporting is unavailable. No `session-logs/` directory exists for ralph-driven sessions.\n386\t4. **Sprint-status.yaml was overwritten.** The parent orchestrator rewrote the entire sprint-status.yaml file (see live log line 4229). While the content was correct, the approach is fragile — it replaced a stale \"Epic Infinity\" placeholder that existed from an earlier bug, which means the file was corrupted at some point.\n387\t\n388\t---\n389\t\n390\t## 6. Lessons Learned\n391\t\n392\t### Patterns to Repeat\n393\t\n394\t- **Single-story-per-iteration pipeline.** The create → dev → review → verify pipeline completing in one iteration is the ideal execution pattern. No context switching, no state management between iterations.\n395\t- **Code review on loop/retry logic.** The stale verdict bug is exactly the kind of state-mutation bug that only appears under iteration. Always review loops and retry logic adversarially.\n396\t- **Building on prior story foundations.** Story 5-2 built directly on 5-1's sequential execution, reusing the same dispatch/checkpoint/error-handling patterns. Incremental stories within an epic pay off in velocity.\n397\t\n398\t### Patterns to Avoid\n399\t\n400\t- **Duplicating dispatch logic.** The 80-line duplication caught in review shows that when loop blocks share behavior with sequential steps, the code should be extracted into shared helpers from the start. The dev phase should anticipate this.\n401\t- **Relying on `.session-issues.md` for ralph sessions.** The file is not being written to. Either fix the mechanism or remove it from the retro requirements.\n402\t- **Trusting `ralph/.state-snapshot.json` as a source of truth.** It lags behind `sprint-status.yaml` and `sprint-state.json`. Use sprint-status.yaml for authoritative state.\n403\t\n404\t---\n405\t\n406\t## 7. Action Items\n407\t\n408\t| # | Action | Priority | Owner | Status |\n409\t|---|--------|----------|-------|--------|\n410\t| 1 | ~~Complete code-review and verify for story 5-1~~ | ~~HIGH~~ | ~~Session 2~~ | DONE |\n411\t| 2 | Fix `codeharness verify` to work without pre-set harness state flags | MEDIUM | Backlog | Open |\n412\t| 3 | Update `src/lib/AGENTS.md` — still missing: agent-dispatch, agent-resolver, session-manager, trace-id | MEDIUM | Next session | Partial |\n413\t| 4 | Fix `codeharness stats --save` to work for non-ralph sessions | MEDIUM | Backlog | Open (escalated from LOW — 3 sessions broken) |\n414\t| 5 | Fix `ralph/.state-snapshot.json` sync — shows 12 done vs 17 actual, E