IRST. This file contains real problems, workarounds, bugs, and observations reported by every subagent that ran this session. These are the raw materials for your retrospective — do not ignore them.\n\nCRITICAL: Run `npx codeharness stats --save` to generate the cost report. Read `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/cost-report.md` and include cost analysis in the retrospective.\n\nCRITICAL: The session issues log contains `## Token Report` sections from each subagent. Aggregate these to understand WHERE tokens were spent inside subagents (not just the parent). Look for:\n- Which subagent phases had the most tool calls?\n- Which subagents read the same files repeatedly?\n- Which Bash commands produced the largest outputs?\n- What redundant operations were reported?\nInclude this subagent-level breakdown in the cost analysis section.\n\nProduce a retrospective that covers:\n1. **Session summary** — which stories were attempted, their outcomes, time spent\n2. **Issues analysis** — categorize and analyze all issues from the session log:\n   - Bugs discovered during implementation or verification\n   - Workarounds applied (tech debt introduced this session)\n   - Code quality concerns raised by reviewers\n   - Verification gaps (escalated ACs, weak evidence)\n   - Tooling/infrastructure problems (sandbox, permissions, CLI issues)\n3. **Cost analysis** — from the cost report:\n   - Total API-equivalent cost this sprint\n   - Cost per phase (which phases are most expensive?)\n   - Cost per story (which stories cost the most and why?)\n   - Wasted spend (no-op sessions, failed verifications, retries)\n   - Cost optimization opportunities\n4. **What went well** — stories completed, bugs fixed, process improvements\n5. **What went wrong** — failures, blockers, stuck stories, wasted iterations\n6. **Lessons learned** — patterns to repeat or avoid\n7. **Action items** — concrete next steps\n\nWrite the retrospective to _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/session-retro-2026-04-03.md.\n\nIf a session retro for today already exists, append to it with a `---` separator and timestamp.\n\nDo NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously.\nDo NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.","agentId":"a01ec4a97ac6a833d","agentType":"general-purpose","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Retrospective written to `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/session-retro-2026-04-03.md` (Session 4, appended with `---` separator).\n\n**Summary of findings:**\n\n- **Stories completed:** 5-3-crash-recovery-resume and 5-4-run-status-commands. Epic 5 is fully done. Sprint at 20/28 (71.4%).\n- **Timeout:** Ralph iteration #9 tried to fit two stories in 30 minutes, timed out after completing 5-3 but losing partial 5-4 work (~$2.50 wasted). Iteration #10 completed 5-4 cleanly.\n- **Bugs caught:** 1 HIGH (--resume flag wired in CLI but never read by engine), 2 MEDIUM. Lower bug count than prior sessions — the engine code is stabilizing.\n- **Estimated session cost:** ~$13.50 (inflated by the timeout retry). Cumulative sprint cost: ~$70.58 for 13 stories (~$5.43/story).\n- **Recurring tech debt escalated:** `formatElapsed` duplication (flagged 4 sessions straight) and 5 dead CLI options both escalated to MEDIUM priority.\n- **State snapshot divergence worsening:** `ralph/.state-snapshot.json` shows 13 done vs 20 actual (35% behind). Escalated to HIGH."}],"totalDurationMs":150695,"totalTokens":56566,"totalToolUseCount":25,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4151,"cache_read_input_tokens":52062,"output_tokens":352,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":4151},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
